1	Use Case [#18]: reject a booking request
1.1	Description
The admin should be able to reject a booking request when they cannot fulfill the appointment.
1.2	Level
Summary.
1.3	Trigger
The admin selects bookings made option.
1.4	Primary Actor
The Primary Actor is the admin who decides which appointments they will be able to fulfil.
1.5	Additional/Supporting Actors
Secondary Actors: 
•	Appointment fulfilment team.
1.6	Stakeholders 
Stakeholders:
•	Appointment fulfilment team.
1.7	Preconditions
The admin [Primary Actor] must have an active internet connection, logged onto the [company.com/shop] site open in the browser there must be appointments made.
1.8	Main Success Scenario
1.	Admin rejects the appointment
2.	Customer is notified that appointment cannot be fulfilled
1.9	Extensions
1.	Exception: ?

1.	Alternative: ?
1.10	Post Conditions
1.10.1	Success End Condition
The admin successfully rejects the booking.
1.10.2	Minimal Guarantees
The admin is logged out of page. The system logs the appointment rejected and updates the bookings page.
1.10.3	Failure End Condition
No bookings are rejected (customer is not notified that their appointment cannot be fulfilled).
1.11	Frequency
Every booking made must either be accepted or rejected.
1.12	Special Requirements
None.
1.12.1	Performance
The admin should be taken to bookings page within 5 seconds.
1.12.2	Security
Only admin can reject bookings.
1.12.3	Usability / Accessibility
Order page must comply with South Africans with Disabilities Act requirements.
Admin must be able to view page in English.
1.12.4	Other
None.
